  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhen sending multiple requests to the slasher to determine if a block proposal is slashable, there is no lock around this request and can lead to race conditions. \r\n\r\nHere is the high level flow:\r\n- Validator makes gRPC request IsSlashableBlock x3\r\n- Slasher checks this request is not slashable by looking in the database\r\n- Slasher updates the database with the slashing request\r\n\r\nThe problem here is that, if there is no lock then the condition at step 2 can be true when step 3 has not occurred yet for some other parallel request.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nlinux amd64\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nalpha.18\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/goerli/medalla/issues/37\r\n",
